1/2/01
  Status:
    view ytse-dpi2:
    view ytse-dpi3:  use to debug new trap/halt problem when using black picture

  BUG (CSCdt08480): DPI: splice timeout in never-timeout mode
      In spctrl.c, timeout!=DPI_TIMEOUT_NEVER is used, instead of timeoutMode!

  BUG: with black pictures, the code sometime will trapped!
    The reason seems to be that in process entry point, after inserting
    a glue picture to resolve field parity conflict, the BG becomes
    seek, ie, not ready!!!
  Fix: moved adjustFgSpliceTime() from insertGluePic() to its callers.

  There are two more bugs that have not been check in:
  - field parity conflict resolution cause BG to become not ready again
      -> reuse CSCdt06540: DPI: problem in field parity conflict
                                across splice point
  - forget to set top field first field in inserted glue pictures 
      -> should use new DDTS
  Both bug fixes should also be checked into the throttle branch.

  Overnight test: dpi1131: with fix of first bug, but not the second.


