1/24/01
  Fix time stamp problem which cause jumping picture around splice point!
  Open GOP case is solved!

  Problem found:
    Need two separate adjustments for:
      - When channel starts up, we assume the first anchor picture has
        decode time of 2 fields, this may be wrong.  In this case,
        we adjust tsDelay and anchor's PTS, instead of the decode time.
      - If the entry anchor's decode time (assume 2 fields) does not match
        with the exit anchor's play time, then we simply adjust entry anchor's
        DTS.
   
  After making the checkin, Emma found that the code is worse at the splice
  point!

  Latest founding with DigiTran:
  - With DiviCom as network and 2 b2b ads, 2.2.4DP1 code has blocks at
    b2b transition.  But latest patch has not!
    Both has glitch when going into the ad.
  - With Harmonic as network and sigle ad, both 2.2.4DP1 and latest patch
    have glitch when going into the ad.  Besides the glitch, we also saw
    white dots and black comb bars at the beginning of ad and the second
    after returning to network.
  - When removing the smart EOS insertion, the glitch is gone!
    But other artifact remains.



